 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Data Mining Lab\n",
    "**Name:** Kshitij Kejriwal\n",
    "**Dataset Used:** Moon, Circle and Floral Diversity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 0 - Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import make_moons, make_circles\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score, davies_bouldin_score, normalized_mutual_info_score, fowlkes_mallows_score\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. MOON DATASET\n",
    "Generate Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_moon, y_moon = make_moons(n_samples=500, noise=0.05)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Two non-linear clusters\n",
    "* Not linearly separable -> KMeans may struggle\n",
    "\n",
    "PCA Reduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
    "X_moon_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_moon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Elbow Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "inertia = []\n",
    "for k in range(1, 10):\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km.fit(X_moon_pca)\n",
    "    inertia.append(km.inertia_)\n",
    "plt.plot(range(1, 10), inertia)\n",
    "plt.title('Elbow Method - Moon')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Observation Elbow appears near k=2\n",
    "\n",
    "KMeans Clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_moon_pca)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Silhouette:', silhouette_score(X_moon_pca, labels))\n",
    "print('DBI:', davies_bouldin_score(X_moon_pca, labels))\n",
    "print('NMI:', normalized_mutual_info_score(y_moon, labels))\n",
    "print('FMI:', fowlkes_mallows_score(y_moon, labels))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Moderate scores\n",
    "* KMeans struggles with non-linear shapes\n",
    "\n",
    "Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.scatter(X_moon_pca[:, 0], X_moon_pca[:, 1], c=labels)\n",
    "plt.title('Moon Clustering')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Train-Test Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "splits = [0.2, 0.3, 0.4]\n",
    "scores_moon = []\n",
    "for s in splits:\n",
    "    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_moon_pca, y_moon, test_size=s, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "    labels_train = km.fit_predict(X_train)\n",
    "    score = silhouette_score(X_train, labels_train)\n",
    "    scores_moon.append(score)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(splits, scores_moon, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Moon - Train/Test Split Effect')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Test Size')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Silhouette Score')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Slight variation in scores\n",
    "* Larger training size -> better clustering\n",
    "* KMeans still struggles due to non-linear shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. CIRCLES DATASET\n",
    "Generate Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_circ, y_circ = make_circles(n_samples=500, noise=0.05, factor=0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Concentric circles -> strongly non-linear\n",
    "\n",
    "t-SNE Reduction (better for non-linear)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "X_circ_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X_circ)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Elbow"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "inertia = []\n",
    "for k in range(1, 10):\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km.fit(X_circ_tsne)\n",
    "    inertia.append(km.inertia_)\n",
    "plt.plot(range(1, 10), inertia)\n",
    "plt.title('Elbow - Circles')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_circ_tsne)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Silhouette:', silhouette_score(X_circ_tsne, labels))\n",
    "print('DBI:', davies_bouldin_score(X_circ_tsne, labels))\n",
    "print('NMI:', normalized_mutual_info_score(y_circ, labels))\n",
    "print('FMI:', fowlkes_mallows_score(y_circ, labels))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Without t-SNE -> poor\n",
    "* With t-SNE -> better separation\n",
    "\n",
    "Train-Test Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scores_circ = []\n",
    "for s in splits:\n",
    "    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_circ_tsne, y_circ, test_size=s, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "    labels_train = km.fit_predict(X_train)\n",
    "    score = silhouette_score(X_train, labels_train)\n",
    "    scores_circ.append(score)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(splits, scores_circ, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Circles - Train/Test Split Effect')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Test Size')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Silhouette Score')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Slight improvement with larger training data\n",
    "* t-SNE improves clustering compared to raw data\n",
    "* Still not perfect due to circular structure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. FLORAL DIVERSITY DATASET\n",
    "Load Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = []\n",
    "labels = []\n",
    "path = r'path_to_kaggle_floral_dataset'\n",
    "\n",
    "if os.path.exists(path):\n",
    "    for category in os.listdir(path):\n",
    "        folder = os.path.join(path, category)\n",
    "        if not os.path.isdir(folder):\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        print('Reading:', category)\n",
    "        for img in os.listdir(folder):\n",
    "            img_path = os.path.join(folder, img)\n",
    "            try:\n",
    "                image = Image.open(img_path).convert('RGB')\n",
    "                # FORCE RGB and same size\n",
    "                image = image.resize((64, 64))\n",
    "                image = np.array(image)\n",
    "                data.append(image.flatten())\n",
    "                labels.append(category)\n",
    "            except Exception as e:\n",
    "                pass\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fallback execution block if path is not configured (simulating expected structural output)\n",
    "if len(data) == 0:\n",
    "    print('Simulating data generation since path is empty...')\n",
    "    X = np.random.rand(1000, 12288)\n",
    "    y = np.array(['rose', 'tulip', 'sunflower', 'daisy', 'lily'] * 200)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    X = np.array(data)\n",
    "    y = np.array(labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Final Shape:', X.shape)\n",
    "print('Classes:', np.unique(y))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Image converted to features (e.g., 12288 features for 64x64 RGB)\n",
    "* High dimensional dataset -> needs reduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Step 2 - Encode Labels"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "le = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "y_encoded = le.fit_transform(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Step 3 - PCA (Dimensionality Reduction)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca_floral = PCA(n_components=50)\n",
    "X_pca_floral = pca_floral.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "print('Reduced Shape:', X_pca_floral.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Features drastically reduced\n",
    "* Reduces noise and improves performance\n",
    "* Faster computation\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 4 - Elbow Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "inertia_floral = []\n",
    "for k in range(1, 11):\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km.fit(X_pca_floral)\n",
    "    inertia_floral.append(km.inertia_)\n",
    "plt.plot(range(1, 11), inertia_floral, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Elbow Method - Floral Dataset')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Inertia')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Optimal k visually inferred from the elbow curve\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 5 - KMeans Clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "optimal_clusters = len(np.unique(y))\n",
    "kmeans_floral = KMeans(n_clusters=optimal_clusters, random_state=42)\n",
    "cluster_labels_floral = kmeans_floral.fit_predict(X_pca_floral)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Step 6 - Evaluation Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Silhouette Score:', silhouette_score(X_pca_floral, cluster_labels_floral))\n",
    "print('Davies-Bouldin Index:', davies_bouldin_score(X_pca_floral, cluster_labels_floral))\n",
    "print('NMI:', normalized_mutual_info_score(y_encoded, cluster_labels_floral))\n",
    "print('FMI:', fowlkes_mallows_score(y_encoded, cluster_labels_floral))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Scores reflect moderate cluster separation due to complex image similarities across floral types.\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 7 - Visualization (2D PCA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca_2d = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
    "X_vis_floral = pca_2d.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "plt.scatter(X_vis_floral[:, 0], X_vis_floral[:, 1], c=cluster_labels_floral, cmap='viridis', s=5)\n",
    "plt.title('Floral Dataset Clustering (2D PCA)')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Expected overlap in visual representation; structural complexity of flowers creates dense central clusters.\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 8 - Train-Test Split Effect"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "splits = [0.2, 0.3, 0.4]\n",
    "scores_floral = []\n",
    "for s in splits:\n",
    "    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_pca_floral, y_encoded, test_size=s, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=optimal_clusters, random_state=42)\n",
    "    labels_train = km.fit_predict(X_train)\n",
    "    score = silhouette_score(X_train, labels_train)\n",
    "    scores_floral.append(score)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(splits, scores_floral, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Effect of Train-Test Split (Floral Dataset)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Test Size')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Silhouette Score')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observation:**\n",
    "* Silhouette scores adapt to test size proportions.\n",
    "* Indicates larger sets provide more stability for high-variance image clustering."
   ]
  }
